20/08/2003
ANKARA, Turkey -- Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan plans to visit Germany and Italy during the first week of September, according to his press office. In Germany, he will meet with Chancellor Gerhard Schroeder and with the leader of the opposition Christian Democratic Union, Angela Merkel. In Italy, Erdogan will meet with Prime Minister Silvio Berlusconi and participate in the Ambrosetti Forum in Villa d'Este. Italy is the current holder of the rotating EU presidency. (Anadolu Agency - 19/08/03)
